When you click on a report in the browse project screen, the project does not get pre-populated in the filter picker on the next screen.  This was probably broken in 3.13 with the new filter picker.  The link even puts the selectedProjectId into the URL.  

It's really an annoyance for the user who has to select the project on that screen even though they just navigated from a particular Browse Project screen.

The service installer does not seem to set the  {{org.apache.jasper.runtime.BodyContentImpl.LIMIT_BUFFER}} property before running tomcat when Jira is installed as a service. I installed Jira and then got this message in the log when I first run it:

{quote}
2008-10-30 10:55:37,305 Thread-1 ERROR [util.system.check.JRA10145Check] WARNING: Apache Tomcat/5.5.26 server and the 'org.apache.jasper.runtime.BodyContentImpl.LIMIT_BUFFER' system property is not set to true! This can result in OutOfMemoryErrors. For more information please see: http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/latest/servers/tomcat55.html
{quote}

